1. ONTHEIA

Pronounced: ON / THEI / A
Discipline: Ontophysics
Intersection: Fundamental Physics + Mathematics + Analytic Metaphysics
Conclusion: Reality is not raw chaos; it possesses structure, order, and intelligibility.

2. COSMION

Pronounced: COS / MI / ON
Discipline: Informational Cosmodynamics
Intersection: Cosmology + Thermodynamics + Information Theory
Conclusion: The universe unfolds as a dynamic process of energy, entropy, and information organization.

3. CAUSALON

Pronounced: CAU / SA / LON
Discipline: Structural Causality
Intersection: Philosophy of Science + Causal Statistics + Dynamical Systems
Conclusion: To understand reality, we must identify real mechanisms, not merely visible correlations.

4. EMERGIA

Pronounced: E / MER / GI / A
Discipline: Science of Emergence
Intersection: Complexity Science + Network Theory + Cybernetics
Conclusion: Many properties of the real arise from interaction, not from isolated parts.

5. BIOSIGNIA

Pronounced: BIO / SIG / NI / A
Discipline: Evolutionary Biosemiotics
Intersection: Evolutionary Biology + Ecology + Semiotics
Conclusion: Life does not merely survive; it interprets signals, adapts, and creates meaning through interaction.

6. NOEMARA

Pronounced: NO / E / MA / RA
Discipline: Neurophenomenology
Intersection: Neuroscience + Phenomenology + Cognitive Science
Conclusion: Consciousness can only be approached properly when objective measurement and subjective experience are studied together.

7. PREDION

Pronounced: PRE / DI / ON
Discipline: Predictive Psychodynamics
Intersection: Cognitive Psychology + Bayesian Inference + Computational Neuroscience
Conclusion: The mind functions largely as a prediction engine, constantly modeling the world and correcting itself through error.

8. LOGORA

Pronounced: LO / GO / RA
Discipline: Language, Logic, and Reality
Intersection: Linguistics + Logic + Philosophy of Language
Conclusion: Human access to reality is profoundly shaped by symbolic structure, naming, and representational limits.

9. ANTHORA

Pronounced: AN / THO / RA
Discipline: Anthropology of Shared Reality
Intersection: Anthropology + History + Sociology
Conclusion: Human beings live simultaneously in physical reality and in collectively constructed symbolic worlds.

10. TECHNEON

Pronounced: TECH / NE / ON
Discipline: Cybernetic Technoagency
Intersection: Engineering + Artificial Intelligence + Robotics + Human–Machine Interaction
Conclusion: Intelligence is no longer purely biological; it is becoming distributed across humans, machines, and systems.

11. ETHARA

Pronounced: E / THA / RA
Discipline: Evolutionary Ethics of Civilization
Intersection: Ethics + Evolutionary Biology + Game Theory + Political Philosophy
Conclusion: Any durable civilization must align power, cooperation, and the reduction of suffering.

12. LIMENOS

Pronounced: LI / ME / NOS
Discipline: Frontier Epistemology
Intersection: Scientific Method + Logic + Measurement Theory + History of Science
Conclusion: The strongest knowledge does not come from pretending certainty, but from disciplined contact with uncertainty and limits.


